===Noun===
'''pedology'''
The sub-discipline of [[soil science]] that:
# Studies soils as a component of natural systems.
# Studies the origin, formation, development and classification of soils.
# Studies the soil profile or [[solum]] in its natural setting.
# Studies the effects of time, parent material, topography, climate and organisms on soil formation.

